text: Events from the year 1993 in Belarus ==Incumbents== * President: not yet established * Chairman of the Supreme Soviet of the Republic of Belarus: Stanislav Shushkevich ==Events== *December 30: The new Beer Lovers Party, formed in August, is officially registered, with Andrey Romashevsky as its Chairman. ==Births== *March 5: Anna Orlik, tennis player ==Deaths== *September 28: Galina Makarova, actress (born 1919) ==See also== * Years in Belarus ==References== Category:Years of the 20th century in Belarus
title: 1993 in Belarus
